import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].mean(), color='red', label='Mean delay = {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].median(), color='green', label='Median delay = {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data['distance'], vert=False)
    ax.set_title('What is the average distance of flights?')
    ax.axvline(x=data['distance'].mean(), color='r', label=f"Mean: {data['distance'].mean():0.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['origin_destination'] = data['origin'] + ' to ' + data['destination']
    origin_destination_counts = data['origin_destination'].value_counts()
    top_10_origin_destination_counts = origin_destination_counts[:10]
    ax = top_10_origin_destination_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Origin to Destination')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    ax.axhline(y=top_10_origin_destination_counts.iloc[0], color='red', linestyle='--', label='Most Common Origin to Destination: {:.2f}'.format(top_10_origin_destination_counts.iloc[0]))
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the most common origin and destination for flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['distance'], data['delay'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Delay')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between distance and delay?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('date').size().reset_index(name='count')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['count'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight dates?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
